  <head>
    <meta content='pelvis.x3d' name='title'/>
    <meta content='pelvis includes sacrum_bone, l_hip_bone, r_hip_bone, pubic_symphysis, coccyx. Note that sacrum_bone is considered part of pelvis anatomy, but the segment named sacrum is modeled in LOA-0 as segment for parent humanoid_root joint' name='description'/>
    <meta content='Don Brutzman, Joe Williams' name='creator'/>
    <meta content='15 March 2026' name='created'/>
    <meta content='24 April 2026' name='modified'/>
    <meta content='In mammals, the bony pelvis has a gap in the middle, significantly larger in females than in males. Their offspring pass through this gap when they are born.' name='info'/>
    <meta content='sacrum belongs with pelvis, specification change needed to make topmost segment virtual' name='TODO'/>
